This paper deals with complexity theoretic aspects of quantum games, specifically one turn quantum refereed games. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.QI (Quantum Physics) are the most likely categories. The paper also involves the use of probability and measurement, which suggests that it could also be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper discusses the players' strategies and winning probabilities, which could be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
